        <name>alarm_id</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>the id of the timer. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>if the timer is not paused, then it will be associated with a TimeAlarms timer. this member stores the id of the timer. when the timer is paused, the TimeAlarms timer does not exist (see above), so this variable is set to 255. this can be used to check whether or not the timer is paused. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
